Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Green, out Tim David Run Out!! 1 run completed. David perishes for the team's cause. Low full toss around leg-stump, Green flicks it to deep mid-wicket and the pair decide to go for the second Abhishek gather cleanly and sends a one bounce throw to Natarajan who takes care of the rest. David was well short of the crease. Tim David run out (Abhishek Sharma/T Natarajan) 16(11) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Marco Jansen to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Markram!! Markram takes a superb running catch. Ishan Kishan comes down the track to a shortish delivery and fails to control his shot as he wafts his blade at it. Ends up slicing it in the air over extra cover due to the extra bounce. The SRH skipper ran back from mid-off, moved to his right and then outstretched his hands to complete the catch. He never took his eyes off the ball. The partnership has been broken! Ishan Kishan c Markram b Marco Jansen 38(31) [4s-3 6s-2]

Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Green, 2 runs, full and wide of off, Green decides to go after it. Thumped over wide long-off after slightly backing away. Jansen runs to his left, catches it with his left hand and pulls it back in. Superb effort there from the tall man. The only question was if he flicked it back in time. He probably did just in time! The umpire rules it in favour of the fielding side. Four runs saved there...

Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Rohit, out Caught by Markram!! Gone! Natarajan removes the dangerous Rohit. Much-needed breakthrough for SRH. Smart bowling from the left-armer. Changed his pace - 120.3kph - and deceived the batsman. Rohit doesn't pick the cutter and is early to close his bat-face as he looks to work this length ball into the leg-side and gets a leading edge that balloons up towards mid-off. A dolly for Markram and he's a happy man. Rohit c Markram b T Natarajan 28(18) [4s-6]

Commentary Text: Arjun Tendulkar to Bhuvneshwar, out Caught by Rohit!! And taken at cover! First scalp for Arjun in IPL. MI win by 14 runs.  The moment Rohit took the catch he pointed his finger towards Arjun and ran towards him in elation. That shows he had faith in Tendulkar junior. Well we have seen it before. Tendulkar under pressure and he has delivered in his first real test. MI have won this by 14 runs. That was a fuller ball, the bat face twisted a little and was taken at cover. Bhuvneshwar c Rohit b Arjun Tendulkar 2(5)

Commentary Text: Green to Markram, out Caught by Hrithik Shokeen!! That's a wicket against the run of play. Was a short ball, Markram went for the pull and this time found the fielder at deep square. The fielder came in and took a low catch as it dipped a little on him but he had it covered. Markram had managed to miss the fielder earlier in the over but not this time. The lack of timing didn't help Markram. Huge wicket for the visitors. Rohit Sharma was elated as he knew how Markram can be a big thorn for them. Markram c Hrithik Shokeen b Green 22(17) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Arjun Tendulkar to Tripathi, wide, why did Menon go for the review still remains a question. Full and sprayed down leg, Tripathi attepmts the glance and there was an appeal from Kishan, then from Arjun and Menon gestured to have heard something, has a chat with the square leg umpire and decides to send it upstairs. UltraEdge didn't spot anything and eventually it is called a wide. "Bit unusual," says Harsha Bhogle on air

Commentary Text: Behrendorff to Harry Brook, out Caught by Suryakumar Yadav!! Behrendorff has the big wicket. The orange in the crowd are stunned. The centurion from last game is gone early. Was that a set up from Behrendorff? Fed him a length ball and then went short into the pitch, Brook goes for the pull but the ball gets big on him, hits the splice of the bat and balloons straight up, SKY runs in from cover and hangs on. Harry Brook c Suryakumar Yadav b Behrendorff 9(7) [4s-2]
